<title>USA: TABLE - Santa Cruz Operation Q3 results.</title>
<headline>TABLE - Santa Cruz Operation Q3 results.</headline>
<dateline>SANTA CRUZ, Calif. 1997-07-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>1997			1996</p>
<p> Shr	 loss	   $0.67  profit	  $0.09</p>
<p> Net	 loss	  24,629  profit	  3,306</p>
<p> Revs			31,166		   54,027</p>
<p>					 6  MONTHS</p>
<p> Shr	 loss	   $0.53    loss	  $0.74</p>
<p> Net	 loss	  19,689    loss	 26,486</p>
<p> Revs		     141,861		  152,676</p>
<p>(All data above 000s except per share numbers)</p>
<p>NOTE: Q3 1997 revenues were impacted by about $23 million of channel inventory reductions due to returns, lower product sales and increased reserves.</p>
<p>Q3 1997 includes a one-time restructuring charge of about $8.4 million or $0.23 per share for reducing headcount, eliminating facilities and writing off some technologies.</p>
<p>9 mos 1996 includes a one-time charge of $35.3 million, or $1.01/shr, due to the acquisition of UnixWare.</p>
